Name: Alex
Video_Title: CBDfx vs CBDistillery Comparison (Disposable CBD Vape Pens)
Description:
choosing which disposable cbd vape pen is the best for you can be difficult. there are a lot of things to take into account- cbd strength, taste, and price point are all deciding factors before you click ‘add to cart’. in this video, we’re looking at two of the most popular cbd vape pens currently on the market, the cbdfx terpene vape pen, and the cbdistillery vape pen. both are strong contenders for your business, but which company is right for you?

for cbdfx it’s their use of terpenes that keep us coming back. we’ve seen cbdfx put some serious thought into how they’re included, and the end result is a disposable vape pen product range that is filled with some of your favorite flavors. they’ve really made a mark with a promise of full flavor at a price point that is kinder than most, backed by all the benefits that terpenes bring to cbd products. studies have suggested that the use of terpenes can increase the efficacy of cbd, and cbdfx has used this to their advantage.

cbdistillery, on the other hand, has focused on the chemicals in the vape juice itself, opting to use tec temper over more traditional carriers like pg or vg. tec temper is a new kind of thinning or liquidating agent and is being touted as the next step for e-liquid carriers. it’s essentially an antioxidant and an anti-irritant and due to the way it behaves when heated, it doesn’t release hazardous or toxic compounds. it’s all-natural and is made with organic ingredients. in essence, this means it’s kind to your throat and lungs while still giving you the ability to create great, billowing clouds at a moment's notice-something that’s rare for a disposable pen.

these are two fantastic products with some serious science backing them up, so what do we prefer? and more importantly, which one is right for you?

the pens themselves are relatively similar- both are easy to use, just puff and play. one nice feature with the cbdistillery pen is its clear chamber, which allows you to see how much oil you have left. with the exception of the branding choices, both pens are well constructed- no issues here.

the differences begin with the strength- cbdfx’s disposable vape pen weighs in at a modest 50mg of cbd per pen, whereas cbdistilleries is 200mg. this means the pricing for the cbdistilleries disposable pen is slightly higher, and this may be something you want to take into consideration. one of the benefits of disposable vape pens is their pocket-friendly pricing when compared to traditional vape kits, and cbdfx has created one of the cheapest options available. this, of course, means you sacrifice on strength, but that’s where cbdfx’s love of terpenes comes into play.

terpenes in cbd create what is known as the ‘entourage effect’. essentially they work in synergy with the other compounds present in the cbd oil, increasing its effectiveness and absorption rate. this means that while each pen contains just 50mg of cbd, that’s 50mg of cbd living it’s the best life and realizing it’s full potential. instead of bumping up the strength, cbdfx has gone back to the drawing board and made what they already have more effective. as the saying goes, there’s always room for improvement, and you can tell from the first puff that cbdfx has taken this to heart.

cbdistillery has chosen an alternative route, focusing on large clouds, big flavor, and bigger doses. the end result is a disposable pen that gives you a surprisingly solid hit that we usually associate with more expensive vaping kits. the choice to use tec temper oil has well and truly paid off, and the cbdistillery disposable vape pen is a joy to use.

flavor-wise, each pen has its own unique characteristics and a range of flavors to choose from. for our money, however, cbdfx just pips cbdistillery to the post on this one. we used gg#4 for cbdistillery and gelato for cbdfx and while they are both full of flavor, cbdfx’s in-depth knowledge of the right terpenes made our decision for us. of course, the taste is always a personal choice, and we wouldn’t presume to tell you what you like, just bear in mind that cbdfx has a proven track record of blending complex flavor profiles to great effect.

as you can see, a lot of rides on personal preference, so which disposable cbd vape pen is best? 
ultimately, the final decision is yours, and we hope this breakdown can help you consider your options. of course, we know which one we prefer- check out the video for our thoughts which pen is best overall, and for a 15% discount on purchases from both cbdistillery and cbdfx!

learn more at https://www.bestdosage.com/

Video_Title: E-cigarettes do not help quit smoking
Description:
the narendra modi government’s proposal to ban e-cigarettes and other electronic nicotine delivery systems (ends) needs to be welcomed as such a move will ensure that indians, especially, children, are kept away from these pernicious products. such a ban has also been recommended by the indian council of medical research (icmr), which called for a “complete prohibition on ends and e-cigarettes in india in the greater interest of protecting public health, in accordance with the precautionary principle preventing public harm from a noxious agent.”
while the tobacco companies promote e-cigarettes as a ‘less risky’ smoking option, some industry documents show that their real goal is to introduce ends products as an alternative to quitting. one company started selling its e-cigarette brand in 2014, promising that it will give the consumers the ‘pleasure of smoking any time anywhere’ (suggesting that they could use the product even at public places, where smoking is banned). 
research suggests that many youngsters, who would otherwise have never started using nicotine, took up conventional smoking after being introduced to e-cigarettes.
